Class HaydukMinhasDiffusivity

java.lang.Object
neqsim.physicalproperties.methods.PhysicalPropertyMethod
neqsim.physicalproperties.methods.liquidphysicalproperties.LiquidPhysicalPropertyMethod

neqsim.physicalproperties.methods.liquidphysicalproperties.diffusivity.HaydukMinhasDiffusivity
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, DiffusivityInterface, PhysicalPropertyMethodInterface, ThermodynamicConstantsInterface
public class HaydukMinhasDiffusivity extends Diffusivity
Hayduk-Minhas diffusivity model for liquid hydrocarbon systems.

This model is more accurate for oil/gas applications than Siddiqi-Lucas, particularly for hydrocarbon solvents. It provides separate correlations for paraffin and aqueous solvents.

References:

  • Hayduk, W. and Minhas, B.S. (1982). "Correlations for prediction of molecular diffusivities in liquids." Can. J. Chem. Eng., 60, 295-299.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Even Solbraa
